## ============================================================
## File: ~/.nanorc
## Date: 2025-11-11
## Purpose: Clean, Linux-friendly Nano configuration for sysadmins
##
## Features & Functions:
##   - Indentation: 2 spaces, tabs converted to spaces, autoindent
##   - Wrapping: Softwrap enabled, line numbers disabled for copy safety
##   - Search: Case-insensitive by default
##   - File handling: Backup files (~), persistent search history, Unix LF endings
##   - Interface: Mouse support, position indicator, smart Home key, smooth scrolling,
##                constant cursor position, visible cursor during selection
##
## Why: Provides a safe, audit-friendly editing environment for Linux configs/logs
##      without overriding Nano’s default keybindings. Keeps workflows predictable
##      for sysadmins and contributors.
##
## ============================================================
## Nano Cheat Sheet (Linux sysadmin–friendly defaults + tweaks)
## ============================================================
## Basic Editing
##   Ctrl+O   Write file (save)
##   Ctrl+X   Exit Nano
##   Ctrl+K   Cut line/selection
##   Ctrl+U   Paste (uncut)
##   Ctrl+J   Justify paragraph
##   Ctrl+T   Spell check (if available)

## Navigation
##   Ctrl+A   Move to beginning of line
##   Ctrl+E   Move to end of line
##   Ctrl+Y   Page up
##   Ctrl+V   Page down
##   Ctrl+_   Go to line number

## Search / Replace
##   Ctrl+W   Search (case-insensitive by default here)
##   Ctrl+\   Search and replace

## Copy/Paste Safe Workflow
##   1. Move cursor to start of text you want to copy
##   2. Press Ctrl+^   → set mark (begin selection)
##   3. Move cursor to end of desired text
##   4. Press Alt+6    → copy selection into cutbuffer
##   5. Move cursor to paste location
##   6. Press Ctrl+U   → paste (uncut)
##
## Notes:
##   - Alt+6 copies without deleting (safe copy)
##   - Ctrl+K cuts (removes text into cutbuffer)
##   - Ctrl+U pastes whatever is in cutbuffer

## Misc
##   Ctrl+C   Show current cursor position
##   Ctrl+G   Help (full keybinding list)

## ============================================================
## Nano Config (Linux defaults + QoL for sysadmins)
## ============================================================

## Indentation
set tabsize 2        # Tabs are 2 spaces wide
set tabstospaces     # Convert tabs to spaces
set autoindent       # Preserve indent on new lines

## Line numbers and wrapping
# set linenumbers     # Disabled: avoids copying line numbers
set softwrap         # Wrap long lines visually (no hard breaks)

## Search
unset casesensitive  # Searches are case-insensitive by default

## File handling
set backup           # Keep backup files (filename~)
set historylog       # Save search/replace history between sessions
set unix             # Save files with Unix line endings (LF only)

## Interface tweaks
set mouse            # Enable mouse support (click to move cursor)
set indicator        # Show position indicator (line/column/percent)
set smarthome        # Home key goes to first non-whitespace, then true beginning
set smooth           # Smooth scrolling instead of jumpy
set showcursor       # Keep cursor visible during selection
set constantshow     # Always show cursor position in status bar
